// create encounter from encounterES for STANDARD type
val encounterSelect = spark.sql("""
select encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific,
current_state_specific_facility,
current_state_specific_service,
cast(row_number() over (partition by personId order by admit_date asc, encounterId asc) as Double) as enc_seq,
datediff(trunc(admit_date,'MM'),(lag(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by admit_date, encounterId)))/365.25 as yearsbetween
from (
    select 
    recordId as encounterId,
    parent as personId,
    admit_date,
    service_category,
    facility.code as facility_code,
    facility.name as facility_name,
    patient_lifecycle.current_state.high_level as current_state_high_level,
    patient_lifecycle.current_state.specific as current_state_specific,
    patient_lifecycle.current_state_facility_specific.specific as current_state_specific_facility,
    patient_lifecycle.current_state_service_specific.specific as current_state_specific_service,
    row_number() over (partition by parent, trunc(admit_date, 'MM') order by admit_date desc, recordId asc) as month_rank
    from encountersES
) where month_rank = 1
""")


encounterSelect.createOrReplaceTempView("encounter")

// ADD THE PROSPECT RECORDS AT THE BEGINNING OF THE LIFECYCLE CHAIN FOR STANDARD TYPE
// add the stub records at the end of the lifecycle chain to track end-dates
val encounterYearsBetween = spark.sql("""
select encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific,
current_state_specific_facility,
current_state_specific_service,
enc_seq,
case when enc_seq = 0.0 then 0 else datediff(admit_date,(lag(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by admit_date, encounterId)))/365.25 end as yearsbetween
from (
select encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific,
current_state_specific_facility,
current_state_specific_service,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween
from encounter
union
select 
'firstAdmit' as encounterId,
personId,
cast(min_admit_month_string as Date) as admit_date,
'' as service_category,
'' as facility_code,
'' as facility_name,
'Prospect' as current_state_high_level,
'Prospect' as current_state_specific,
'Prospect' as current_state_specific_facility,
'Prospect' as current_state_specific_service,
cast(0 as Double) as enc_seq,
0 as yearsbetween
from encounter e cross join dateRanges d
group by e.personId,cast(min_admit_month_string as Date)
UNION
-- stub records for most recent date - for setting current status
select 
'lastAdmit' as encounterId,
personId,
--cast(max_admit_month_string as Date) as admit_date,
max_admit_month_next as admit_date,
'' as service_category,
'' as facility_code,
'' as facility_name,
'UNKNOWN' as current_state_high_level,
'UNKNOWN' as current_state_specific,
'UNKNOWN' as current_state_specific_facility,
'UNKNOWN' as current_state_specific_service,
cast(max(enc_seq) + 1 as Double) as enc_seq,
datediff(max_admit_month_next,max(admit_date))/365.25 as yearsbetween
from encounter e cross join dateRanges d
group by e.personId,max_admit_month_next

)
""")
encounterYearsBetween.cache
encounterYearsBetween.createOrReplaceTempView("encounterYearsBetween")
// encounterYearsBetween.show()

// FULL LIFECYCLE FOR STANDARD (NOT SERVICE-SPECIFIC OR FACILITY-SPECIFIC) STATES
// add existing, prospect and lapsed statuses
// EXISTING for all dates more than 3 months after previous encounter
// LAPSED for all dates more than 1 year after previous encounter
// PROSPECT for all dates more than 3 years after previous encounter
val encounterFullLifecycle = spark.sql("""
-- EXISTING for all dates more than 3 months after previous encounter
select 
concat('Existing_' , cast(admit_date as varchar(20)),'_',cast(previous_admit_date as varchar(20))) as encounterId,
personId,
case
    -- when the estimated admit date of the "non-encounter" lifecycle event is past the threshold cutoff assign it the standard value
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) >= 0.25 then
        date_add(previous_admit_date,(0.25 * 365.25))
    -- when the estimated admit date of the "non-encounter" lifecycle event is NOT past the threshold cutoff 
    -- then bump it up to the next month, but only if that next month is not past the admit date
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 0.25 
--    and date_add(previous_admit_date,((0.25 * 365.25) + (0.083 * 365.25))) > admit_date then
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((0.25 * 365.25) + (0.083 * 365.25))),admit_date) < 0  then
        date_add(previous_admit_date,((0.25 * 365.25) + (0.083 * 365.25)))
    else 
        date_add(previous_admit_date,(0.25 * 365.25))
end as admit_date,
'' as service_category,
'' as facility_code,
'' as facility_name,
'Patient' as current_state_high_level,
'Existing Patient' as current_state_specific,
enc_seq - 0.75 as enc_seq,
case 
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) >= 0.25
        then datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 0.25 
--    and date_add(previous_admit_date,((0.25 * 365.25) + (0.083 * 365.25))) > admit_date then
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((0.25 * 365.25) + (0.083 * 365.25))),admit_date) < 0  then
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25 + (0.083 * 365.25)),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25 
    else 
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
end as yearsbetween
from (
    select encounterId,personId,admit_date,enc_seq,yearsbetween,
    lag(admit_date,1,null) over (partition by personId order by admit_date, enc_seq) previous_admit_date,
    lag(e.current_state_specific,1,'UNKNOWN') over (partition by personId order by admit_date, enc_seq) previous_state_specific,max_admit_month
    from encounterYearsBetween e cross join dateRanges
    -- where yearsbetween > 0.25 and enc_seq > 1 and current_state_specific <> 'Existing Patient'
) where yearsbetween > 0.25 and enc_seq > 1 and  previous_state_specific <> 'Existing Patient' -- and current_state_specific <> 'Existing Patient'
and date_add(previous_admit_date,0.25 * 365.25) <= max_admit_month
UNION
-- LAPSED for all dates more than 1 year
select 
concat('Lapsed_' , cast(admit_date as varchar(20))) as encounterId,
personId,
case
    -- when the estimated admit date of the "non-encounter" lifecycle event is past the threshold cutoff assign it the standard value
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) >= 1 then
        date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25)
    -- when the estimated admit date of the "non-encounter" lifecycle event is NOT past the threshold cutoff 
    -- then bump it up to the next month, but only if that next month is not past the admit date
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 1 
--    and date_add(previous_admit_date,((1 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))) > admit_date then
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((1 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))),admit_date) < 0  then
        date_add(previous_admit_date,((1 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))) 
    else 
        date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25)
end as admit_date,
'' as service_category,
'' as facility_code,
'' as facility_name,
'Patient' as current_state_high_level,
'Lapsed Patient' as current_state_specific,
enc_seq - 0.5 as enc_seq,
case 
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) >= 1
        then datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 1 
--    and date_add(previous_admit_date,((1 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))) > admit_date then
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((1 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))),admit_date) < 0  then
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25 + (365.25/12)),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25 
    else 
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
end as yearsbetween
from (
select encounterId,personId,admit_date,enc_seq,yearsbetween,
lag(admit_date,1,null) over (partition by personId order by admit_date, enc_seq) previous_admit_date,max_admit_month
from encounterYearsBetween cross join dateRanges
) where yearsbetween > 1 and enc_seq > 1
and date_add(previous_admit_date,1 * 365.25) <= max_admit_month
UNION
-- PROSPECT for all dates more than 3 years after previous encounter
select 
concat('Prospect_' , cast(admit_date as varchar(20))) as encounterId,
personId,
case
    -- when the estimated admit date of the "non-encounter" lifecycle event is past the threshold cutoff assign it the standard value
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) >= 3 then
        date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25)
    -- when the estimated admit date of the "non-encounter" lifecycle event is NOT past the threshold cutoff 
    -- then bump it up to the next month, but only if that next month is not past the admit date
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 3 
--    and date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))) > admit_date then
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))),admit_date) < 0  then
        date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))) 
    else 
        date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25)
end as admit_date,
'' as service_category,
'' as facility_code,
'' as facility_name,
'Prospect' as current_state_high_level,
'Prospect' as current_state_specific,
enc_seq - 0.25 as enc_seq,
case 
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) >= 3
        then datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 3 
--    and date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))) > admit_date then
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))),admit_date) < 0  then
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25 + (365.25/12)),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25 
    else 
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
end as yearsbetween
from (
select encounterId,personId,admit_date,enc_seq,yearsbetween,
lag(admit_date,1,null) over (partition by personId order by admit_date, enc_seq) previous_admit_date,max_admit_month
from encounterYearsBetween e cross join dateRanges
) where yearsbetween > 3 and enc_seq > 1
and date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25) <= max_admit_month
UNION
select 
encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween
from encounterYearsBetween
""")
encounterFullLifecycle.cache
encounterFullLifecycle.createOrReplaceTempView("encounterFullLifecycle")
//encounterFullLifecycle.show()

// final sequenced and formatted full lifecycle for STANDARD lifecycle type (not facility or service specific)
val encounterSequencedLifecycle = spark.sql("""
select
encounterId,
personId,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween,
admit_date,
date_format(start_date,'yyyy-MM-dd') as start_date,
date_format(end_date,'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss') as end_date,
start_date_epoch,
end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific,
previous_state_high_level,
previous_state_specific,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
same_state,
row_number() over (partition by personId order by enc_seq) as enc_seq_int
from (
select
encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
trunc(admit_date,'MM') as start_date,
from_unixtime(unix_timestamp(trunc(lead(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId),'MM')) - 1) as end_date,
unix_timestamp(trunc(admit_date,'MM')) * 1000 as start_date_epoch,
(unix_timestamp(trunc(lead(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId),'MM')) - 1) * 1000 as end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific,
lag(current_state_high_level,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) as previous_state_high_level,
lag(current_state_specific,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) as previous_state_specific,
case when lag(current_state_specific,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) = current_state_specific 
and enc_seq <> 0.0 and current_state_specific not in ('Service Cross-Sell','Facility Cross-Sell')
then 1 else 0 end as same_state,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween,
case when current_state_specific = 'Service Cross-Sell' then service_category else '' end service_category,
case when current_state_specific = 'Facility Cross-Sell' then facility_code else '' end as facility_code,
case when current_state_specific = 'Facility Cross-Sell' then facility_name else '' end facility_name
from encounterFullLifecycle
) where encounterId <> 'lastAdmit'
-- there are still a few extraneous records in there that are not valid.  we will eliminate them for now
and start_date_epoch < end_date_epoch
""")
encounterSequencedLifecycle.cache
encounterSequencedLifecycle.createOrReplaceTempView("encounterSequencedLifecycle")

// collapsed lifecycle data with all intermediary "existing patient" states collapsed down for STANDARD (not facility or service specific) lifecycle type
val encounterCollapsedLifecycle = spark.sql("""
select
same_state,
encounterId,
e.personId,
e.enc_seq,
e.enc_seq_int,
yearsbetween,
admit_date,
date_format(start_date,'yyyy-MM-dd') as start_date,
date_format(coalesce(r.range_end_date,end_date),'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss') as end_date,
start_date_epoch,
coalesce(r.range_end_date_epoch,end_date_epoch) as end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific,
previous_state_high_level,
previous_state_specific,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name
from encounterSequencedLifecycle e
left join (
    -- for all not-same_state rows get the minimum non-same-state row number greater than the current row number
    select c.personid,c.enc_seq_int, min(n.enc_seq_int) as next_seq_int, min(previous_end_date) as range_end_date,min(previous_end_date_epoch) as range_end_date_epoch
    from 
    -- all rows at beginning of chain 
    (select personId, enc_seq_int from (select personid,enc_seq_int,same_state, lead(same_state) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as next_state from encounterSequencedLifecycle) where same_state = 0 and next_state = 1) c
    -- all rows now in same_state
    join
    (select personId, same_state, enc_seq_int, 
    lag(end_date) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as previous_end_date,
    lag(end_date_epoch) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as previous_end_date_epoch
    from encounterSequencedLifecycle) n on n.personId = c.personId and c.enc_seq_int < n.enc_seq_int and n.same_state = 0
    group by c.personid,c.enc_seq_int
) r on r.personid = e.personid and r.enc_seq_int = e.enc_seq_int
where same_state = 0
""")
encounterCollapsedLifecycle.cache
encounterCollapsedLifecycle.createOrReplaceTempView("encounterCollapsedLifecycle")

// final sequenced and formatted full lifecycle for SERVICE-SPECIFIC lifecycle type
val encounterSequencedLifecycle_Service = spark.sql("""
select
encounterId,
personId,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween,
admit_date,
date_format(start_date,'yyyy-MM-dd') as start_date,
date_format(end_date,'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss') as end_date,
start_date_epoch,
end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific_service,
previous_state_high_level,
previous_state_specific_service,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
same_state,
row_number() over (partition by personId order by enc_seq) as enc_seq_int
from (
select
encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
trunc(admit_date,'MM') as start_date,
from_unixtime(unix_timestamp(trunc(lead(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId),'MM')) - 1) as end_date,
unix_timestamp(trunc(admit_date,'MM')) * 1000 as start_date_epoch,
(unix_timestamp(trunc(lead(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId),'MM')) - 1) * 1000 as end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific_service,
lag(current_state_high_level,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) as previous_state_high_level,
lag(current_state_specific_service,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) as previous_state_specific_service,
case when lag(current_state_specific_service,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) = current_state_specific_service
and enc_seq <> 0.0 and current_state_specific_service not in ('Service Cross-Sell','Facility Cross-Sell')
then 1 else 0 end as same_state,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween,
case when current_state_specific_service = 'Service Cross-Sell' then service_category else '' end service_category,
case when current_state_specific_service = 'Facility Cross-Sell' then facility_code else '' end as facility_code,
case when current_state_specific_service = 'Facility Cross-Sell' then facility_name else '' end facility_name
from encounterFullLifecycle_Service
) where encounterId <> 'lastAdmit'
-- there are still a few extraneous records in there that are not valid.  we will eliminate them for now
and start_date_epoch < end_date_epoch
""")

// collapsed lifecycle data with all intermediary "existing patient" states collapsed down for SERVICE SPECIFIC lifecycle type
val encounterCollapsedLifecycle_Service = spark.sql("""
select
same_state,
encounterId,
e.personId,
e.enc_seq,
e.enc_seq_int,
yearsbetween,
admit_date,
date_format(start_date,'yyyy-MM-dd') as start_date,
date_format(coalesce(r.range_end_date,end_date),'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss') as end_date,
start_date_epoch,
coalesce(r.range_end_date_epoch,end_date_epoch) as end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific_service as current_state_specific,
previous_state_high_level,
previous_state_specific_service as previous_state_specific,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name
from encounterSequencedLifecycle_Service e
left join (
    -- for all not-same_state rows get the minimum non-same-state row number greater than the current row number
    select c.personid,c.enc_seq_int, min(n.enc_seq_int) as next_seq_int, min(previous_end_date) as range_end_date,min(previous_end_date_epoch) as range_end_date_epoch
    from 
    -- all rows at beginning of chain 
    (select personId, enc_seq_int from (select personid,enc_seq_int,same_state, lead(same_state) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as next_state from encounterSequencedLifecycle_Service) where same_state = 0 and next_state = 1) c
    -- all rows now in same_state
    join
    (select personId, same_state, enc_seq_int, 
    lag(end_date) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as previous_end_date,
    lag(end_date_epoch) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as previous_end_date_epoch
    from encounterSequencedLifecycle_Service) n on n.personId = c.personId and c.enc_seq_int < n.enc_seq_int and n.same_state = 0
    group by c.personid,c.enc_seq_int
) r on r.personid = e.personid and r.enc_seq_int = e.enc_seq_int
where same_state = 0
""")

    -- when the estimated admit date of the "non-encounter" lifecycle event is NOT past the threshold cutoff 
    -- then bump it up to the next month, but only if that next month is not past the admit date
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 3 
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))),admit_date) < 0  then
        date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))) 
    else 
        date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25)
end as admit_date,
'' as service_category,
'' as facility_code,
'' as facility_name,
'Prospect' as current_state_high_level,
'Prospect' as current_state_specific_facility,
enc_seq - 0.25 as enc_seq,
case 
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) >= 3
        then datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
    when (datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25) < 3 
     and datediff(date_add(previous_admit_date,((3 * 365.25) + (365.25/12))),admit_date) < 0  then
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25 + (365.25/12)),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25 
    else 
        datediff(trunc(date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25),'MM'),previous_admit_date)/365.25
end as yearsbetween
from (
select encounterId,personId,admit_date,enc_seq,yearsbetween,
lag(admit_date,1,null) over (partition by personId order by admit_date, enc_seq) previous_admit_date,max_admit_month
from encounterYearsBetween_Facility e cross join dateRanges
) where yearsbetween > 3 and enc_seq > 1
and date_add(previous_admit_date,3 * 365.25) <= max_admit_month
UNION
select 
encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific_facility,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween
from encounterYearsBetween_Facility
""")

// final sequenced and formatted full lifecycle for FACILITY-SPECIFIC lifecycle type
val encounterSequencedLifecycle_Facility = spark.sql("""
select
encounterId,
personId,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween,
admit_date,
date_format(start_date,'yyyy-MM-dd') as start_date,
date_format(end_date,'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss') as end_date,
start_date_epoch,
end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific_facility,
previous_state_high_level,
previous_state_specific_facility,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name,
same_state,
row_number() over (partition by personId order by enc_seq) as enc_seq_int
from (
select
encounterId,
personId,
admit_date,
trunc(admit_date,'MM') as start_date,
from_unixtime(unix_timestamp(trunc(lead(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId),'MM')) - 1) as end_date,
unix_timestamp(trunc(admit_date,'MM')) * 1000 as start_date_epoch,
(unix_timestamp(trunc(lead(admit_date,1,cast('1900-01-01' as date)) over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId),'MM')) - 1) * 1000 as end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific_facility,
lag(current_state_high_level,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) as previous_state_high_level,
lag(current_state_specific_facility,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) as previous_state_specific_facility,
case when lag(current_state_specific_facility,1,'Prospect') over (partition by personId order by enc_seq, encounterId) = current_state_specific_facility
and enc_seq <> 0.0 and current_state_specific_facility not in ('Service Cross-Sell','Facility Cross-Sell')
then 1 else 0 end as same_state,
enc_seq,
yearsbetween,
case when current_state_specific_facility = 'Service Cross-Sell' then service_category else '' end service_category,
case when current_state_specific_facility = 'Facility Cross-Sell' then facility_code else '' end as facility_code,
case when current_state_specific_facility = 'Facility Cross-Sell' then facility_name else '' end facility_name
from encounterFullLifecycle_Facility
) where encounterId <> 'lastAdmit'
-- there are still a few extraneous records in there that are not valid.  we will eliminate them for now
and start_date_epoch < end_date_epoch
""")

// collapsed lifecycle data with all intermediary "existing patient" states collapsed down for FACILITY SPECIFIC lifecycle type
val encounterCollapsedLifecycle_Facility = spark.sql("""
select
same_state,
encounterId,
e.personId,
e.enc_seq,
e.enc_seq_int,
yearsbetween,
admit_date,
date_format(start_date,'yyyy-MM-dd') as start_date,
date_format(coalesce(r.range_end_date,end_date),'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss') as end_date,
start_date_epoch,
coalesce(r.range_end_date_epoch,end_date_epoch) as end_date_epoch,
current_state_high_level,
current_state_specific_facility as current_state_specific,
previous_state_high_level,
previous_state_specific_facility as previous_state_specific,
service_category,
facility_code,
facility_name
from encounterSequencedLifecycle_Facility e
left join (
    -- for all not-same_state rows get the minimum non-same-state row number greater than the current row number
    select c.personid,c.enc_seq_int, min(n.enc_seq_int) as next_seq_int, min(previous_end_date) as range_end_date,min(previous_end_date_epoch) as range_end_date_epoch
    from 
    -- all rows at beginning of chain
    (select personId, enc_seq_int from (select personid,enc_seq_int,same_state, lead(same_state) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as next_state from encounterSequencedLifecycle_Facility) where same_state = 0 and next_state = 1) c
    -- all rows now in same_state
    join
    (select personId, same_state, enc_seq_int, 
    lag(end_date) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as previous_end_date,
    lag(end_date_epoch) over (partition by personid order by enc_seq_int) as previous_end_date_epoch
    from encounterSequencedLifecycle_Facility) n on n.personId = c.personId and c.enc_seq_int < n.enc_seq_int and n.same_state = 0
    group by c.personid,c.enc_seq_int
) r on r.personid = e.personid and r.enc_seq_int = e.enc_seq_int
where same_state = 0
""")

encounterCollapsedLifecycle_Facility.createOrReplaceTempView("encounterCollapsedLifecycle_Facility")
